  {
    "id": "ercot_system_as_capacity_monitor",
    "name": "ERCOT System AS Capacity Monitor",
    "description": "Real-time ERCOT totals for ancillary services and capacity available for dispatch in SCED (Security-Constrained Economic Dispatch).\n\n***Acronym Assistance***\n* RRS - Responsive Reserves\n* CLRs - Controllable Load Resources\n* FFR - Fast Frequency Response\n* PFR- Primary Frequency Response\n* UFR - Under Frequency Relay\n* ESR - Energy Storage Resource\n* ECRS - ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service\n* QSGR - Quick Start Generation Resource\n* ONSC - ONLINE Synchronous Condenser (resource status)\n* PRC - Physical Responsive Capability\n* BP - Base Point\n* EMR - Available for commitment or dispatch only for ERCOT-declared Emergency Conditions\n* OUTL - Offline Unavailable\n* EMRSWGR - Offline Available Only for Emergency Condition\n\nImplemented on December 5th, 2025, as part of ERCOT's RTC+B project, which substantially reworked the previous AS Capacity Monitor table."
