  {
    "id": "ercot_prc",
    "name": "ERCOT PRC",
    "description": "Physical Responsive Capability (PRC) in ERCOT. New data is published on an irregular frequency, but is generally multiple times per minute.\n\nPRC is the generation and load resources that can quickly respond to sudden changes on the system. Events such as the unexpected trip of a large generator rely on fast response of other resources to fill the gap. The PRC is a measure of those other resources' capability. "
  },
  {
    "id": "ercot_real_time_adders",
    "name": "ERCOT Real Time Adders",
    "description": "The Real-Time Reliability Deployment Price Adders (RTRDPAs) for energy and each ancillary service, for each SCED run in ERCOT.\n\nThis dataset also includes:\n* System Lambda (\u03bb), which is the Shadow Price for the system-wide Power Balance constraint\n* Total RUC/RMR Low Dispatch Limit (LDL) relaxed\n* Deployed Load Resource MWs that are added to Demand\n* Energy Storage Resource Charging MWs that are added to Demand\n* Total Low Sustained Limit (LSL)\n* Total High Sustained Limit (HSL)\n\nThis dataset was implemented on December 5th, 2025, as part of ERCOT's RTC+B project, which modified many existing datasets related to ancillary services and system capacity while also introducing new reports."
  },
  {
    "id": "ercot_real_time_adders_and_reserves",
    "name": "ERCOT Real Time Adders And Reserves",
    "description": "\u26a0\ufe0f Due to large changes in AS data post RTC+C, we've decide to retired this dataset. The historical data is still available, but will no longer receive updates.\nThe dataset id of the new dataset is [ercot_real_time_adders](https://www.gridstatus.io/datasets/ercot_real_time_adders). \n\n___\n\nERCOT Real-Time ORDC and Reliability Deployment Price Adders and Reserves by SCED Interval\n\nThis ERCOT dataset contains the real-time adders and reserve elements in each run of SCED. Deployed ERS and load resources are included, as are RUC/RMR LDL relaxed, and total LASL and HASL.\n\nThere are a few common elements in the columm names from ERCOT that can assist in understanding and using this dataset. Let's use RTORPA as an example:\n\n* RT = Real-Time\n* OR = Operating Reserves\n* PA = Price Adder \n\nCollectively, these create the column RTORPA, or the Real-Time On-Line Reserve Price Adder. If you replace the OR with OFF you have the Real-Time Off-Line Reserve Price Adder. Swapping in CAP for PA changes the column from Price to Capacity, so RTOFFCAP is Real-Time Off-Line Capacity. Following from these conventions, the Real-Time On-Line Reliability Deployment Price Adder is RTORDPA.\n\nAdditional acronyms include:\n\n* CLR = Controllable Load Resource\n* RMR = Reliability Must Run\n* REG = Regulation\n* RRS = Responsive Reserve\n* ECRS = ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service\n* RUC = Reliabililty Unit Commitment"
  },
  {
    "id": "ercot_real_time_as_monitor",
    "name": "ERCOT Real Time AS Monitor",
    "description": "\u26a0\ufe0f Due to large changes in AS data post RTC+C, we've decide to retire this dataset. The historical data is still available, but will no longer receive updates.\nThe dataset id of the new dataset is [ercot_system_as_capacity_monitor](https://www.gridstatus.io/datasets/ercot_system_as_capacity_monitor). \n___\n\nReal Time AS Monitor as reported by ERCOT. Includes capacity and responsibility. Updates ~10 seconds."
